; Regression test: Zerosum plugin duplicate Open directive
;
; Bug: The zerosum plugin would create Open directives for target accounts
; even when those accounts were already opened elsewhere in the ledger,
; causing E1002 "Account is already open" errors.
;
; Root cause: The native zerosum plugin wasn't checking for existing Open
; directives before creating new ones for matched target accounts.

option "operating_currency" "USD"

; Pre-existing Open for the zerosum target account
2020-01-01 open Assets:Transfer
2020-01-01 open Assets:ZSA-Matched:Transfer  ; Already opened!
2020-01-01 open Assets:Bank:Checking
2020-01-01 open Assets:Bank:Savings

plugin "beancount_reds_plugins.zerosum.zerosum" "{
    'zerosum_accounts': {
        'Assets:Transfer': ('Assets:ZSA-Matched:Transfer', 7),
    },
}"

; Transfer out
2024-01-15 * "Transfer to savings"
  Assets:Bank:Checking    -1000 USD
  Assets:Transfer          1000 USD

; Matching transfer in (within 7 days)
2024-01-17 * "Transfer received"
  Assets:Transfer         -1000 USD
  Assets:Bank:Savings      1000 USD

; The zerosum plugin should:
; 1. Match the two transfers (they net to zero)
; 2. Move matched postings to Assets:ZSA-Matched:Transfer
; 3. NOT create a duplicate Open for Assets:ZSA-Matched:Transfer
